MPI for Python (mpi4py) Quick Start Guide

MPI for Python (mpi4py) provides Python bindings for the Message Passing Interface (MPI) standard, enabling Python applications to utilize multiple processors on workstations, clusters, and supercomputers.

For comprehensive documentation, please refer to the official mpi4py documentation.

Installation

Using Anaconda (Recommended)
If you're using an Anaconda environment, you can install mpi4py using the following command:
conda install -c conda-forge mpi4py

Without Anaconda
If Anaconda is not available, you can install mpi4py using other methods described in the https://mpi4py.readthedocs.io/en/stable/install.html.

